06/05/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Belgrade special court will issue the verdicts in the Zoran Djindjic assassination case on May 23rd, court council head Nata Mesarevic said Friday (May 4th).
Earlier the same day, the court finished hearing final statements from the defendants, most of whom pleaded not guilty.
Twelve ex-members of the disbanded Serbian Unit for Special Operations and the criminal Zemun Clan have been indicted in the case, which has continued for three and a half years.
Djindjic was shot dead in front of the Serbian government building on March 12th, 2003.
(Danas - 05/05/07;
Tanjug, Beta - 04/05/07)
